<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880224-0151 </DOCNO><HL> Diamond Crystal Salt Unit Sale </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DSLT </CO><IN> TNM </IN><G> JUS </G><DATELINE> ST. CLAIR, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Diamond Crystal Salt Co. said the Justice Department won't oppose on antitrust grounds the sale of its salt division to International Salt Co.    International Salt, a unit of Akzo N.V. of the Netherlands, a chemical concern, agreed to pay $65 million in cash and the assumption of certain liabilities for Diamond Crystal's unit. Diamond Crystal said it expects to close the deal by March 31. </TEXT></DOC>